configuring thunderbird to use the stanford ldap directory stanford tech commons go to the stanford university web site home a community space for sharing technical knowledge join us learn more mailing list search search this site click on search for better search options or log in to add something to the commons configuring thunderbird to use the stanford ldap directory posted july 25th 2008 by john bickar in miscellaneous tutorial email ldap thunderbird you can configure thunderbird or any e mail client to pull name and e mail information from the stanford ldap directory to do this go to tools options thunderbird preferences on the mac click the composition tab click the addressing tab check the box that says directory server click edit directories click add type stanford in the name box type ldap stanford edu in the hostname box type cn people dc stanford dc edu in the base dn box type 389 in the port number box leave use secure connection ssl unchecked click ok then click ok again be sure to choose stanford from the directory server drop down menu then click ok one final time now when you type in a person's name in the to cc or bcc field s it will auto complete your entry from the public stanford ldap server the information gathered on these pages is generated by the stanford university community with significant support from the academic technology specialist program sulair information center su webmasters stanford video and multimedia group and it services unless otherwise specified it is licensed under a creative commons attribution noncommercial share alike 3.0 license creative commons license
